# Neovim Cheatsheet — Custom IDE Setup
# Leader key: Space

# ==================== BASICS ====================

# Navigation
h / j / k / l                Move left/down/up/right
w / b                        Next/previous word
0 / $                        Start/end of line
gg / G                       Top/bottom of file
Ctrl+d / Ctrl+u              Half-page down/up

# Editing
i / a                        Insert before/after cursor
o / O                        New line below/above
dd / yy / p                  Delete/yank/paste line
u / Ctrl+r                   Undo/redo
ciw / diw                    Change/delete inner word
gcc                          Toggle comment (line)
gc                           Toggle comment (selection, visual mode)

# Search
/ pattern                    Search forward
n / N                        Next/previous match

# ==================== FILE MANAGEMENT ====================

Ctrl+p                       Open Neo-tree (file explorer)
q                            Close Neo-tree panel
a                            New file (in Neo-tree)
d                            Delete file (in Neo-tree)
r                            Rename file (in Neo-tree)
Enter                        Open file (in Neo-tree)

Ctrl+f                       Find files (Telescope)
Ctrl+l                       Live grep (Telescope)

# ==================== AUTOCOMPLETION (blink.cmp) ====================

# Completion popup appears automatically as you type
Ctrl+Space                   Trigger completion manually
Ctrl+n / Ctrl+p              Next/previous item
Ctrl+y / Enter               Accept completion
Ctrl+e                       Dismiss completion

# ==================== TERMINAL ====================

Ctrl+\                       Toggle floating terminal
Space t f                    Float terminal
Space t h                    Horizontal terminal
Space t v                    Vertical terminal

# ==================== GIT (gitsigns) ====================

]h / [h                      Next/prev git hunk
Space g s                    Stage hunk
Space g r                    Reset hunk
Space g p                    Preview hunk
Space g b                    Blame line
Space g d                    Diff this file

# ==================== FORMATTING (conform) ====================

# Format-on-save is enabled automatically
Space c f                    Format buffer manually

# Formatters by language:
# Python    — isort + black
# C/C++     — clang-format
# Shell     — shfmt
# Markdown  — prettier
# JSON/YAML — prettier

# ==================== DEBUGGING (DAP) ====================

Space d b                    Toggle breakpoint
Space d c                    Continue
Space d i                    Step into
Space d o                    Step over
Space d r                    Open REPL
Space d u                    Toggle debug UI

# ==================== CMAKE ====================

Space c g                    CMake generate
Space c b                    CMake build
Space c r                    CMake run
Space c t                    Select build target

# ==================== DIAGNOSTICS (trouble) ====================

Space x x                    Workspace diagnostics
Space x d                    Buffer diagnostics
Space x l                    Location list
Space x q                    Quickfix list
Space x t                    TODOs
Space f t                    Find TODOs (Telescope)

# ==================== MARKDOWN ====================

Space m p                    Toggle markdown preview (opens in browser)

# ==================== AI / CLAUDE ====================

# Claude Code (claudecode.nvim) — requires `claude` CLI
Space a c                    Toggle Claude Code terminal
Space a f                    Focus Claude Code
Space a r                    Resume previous conversation
Space a m                    Select model
Space a b                    Add current buffer to context
Space a s                    Send selection to Claude (visual mode)
Space a a                    Accept diff from Claude
Space a d                    Deny diff from Claude

# ==================== WHICH-KEY ====================

# Press Space and wait — popup shows all available keybindings
# Groups: a=AI/Claude  c=Code/CMake  d=Debug  g=Git  m=Markdown  t=Terminal  x=Diagnostics  f=Find

# ==================== LSP (works automatically per language) ====================

# Enabled servers:
# Python    — pyright + ruff
# C/C++     — clangd (with clang-tidy)
# Bash/Zsh  — bash-language-server

gd                           Go to definition
gr                           Go to references
K                            Hover docs
Space rn                     Rename symbol (if configured)
